rn African nation is in the process of vaccinating 2,000 people with the vaccine, developed by the Oxford Jenner Institute, which is already being evaluated in Britain, where 4,000 participants have enrolled in the trial. Africa News Vanguard South Africa will roll out the first African first coronavirus vaccine trial this week, the university leading the pilot said Tuesday, as the country grapples with the highest number of cases in Africa. The vaccine, developed by the Oxford Jenner Institute, is already being evaluated in Britain, where 4,000 participants… June 24, 2020 In "Coronavirus Updates" THE worst fears of Nigerians about the coronavirus disease (COVID-19) have not yet come to pass essentially because the country has so far been spared an exponential increase in COVID-19 case numbers. May 2, 2020 In "Coronavirus Updates" Professor Charles Obadiah Wambebe is a Professor of Pharmacology and a Missionary, who served as the pioneer Director-General for the National Institute of Pharmaceutical Research and Development (NIPRD) from 1989-2001, Lecturer and Professor, Ahmadu Bello University, Zaria. He has also served as President of the West African Society of Pharmacology… May 14, 2020 In "News"